2064.subject: HPWE
2064.course_title_long: Phys Ed for Elem Sch Child Lab
2064.descrlong: 32 hours of contact with preschool and elementary school children, focusing on the neurological foundations for movement for all children from a growth and development perspective.  Emphasizes physical activity and programmatic organization in the gymnasium and on the playground as it relates to problem solving and academic success; multicultural approaches to movement, moral development, and self image; movement exploration, body/spatial awareness; and non-locomotor skills.  Also offered online. (Offered every spring in even years.)
